    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of an order containing over 350,000 known living species of insects having the upper pair of wings converted into hard sheaths or wing-cases (elytra) that close over the back, and protect the lower or true wings, which most species are able to use in flight.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
